author: Sabrina Ullman WDIO
title: Sabrina Ullman: Finally decent rainfall
text:
Sabrina Ullman: Finally decent rainfall
After the second-driest September and more dry conditions for the first third of October, we are finally getting rain. Light rain will become heavier and more widespread late tonight, continuing into Sunday morning. Total accumulation tonight and Sunday is expected to be half an inch to three-quarters of an inch for most of the Northland.
Overnight lows will be in the upper 30s to low 40s. Patchy fog is likely, clearing by 10 am. A calm wind will become northwest after midnight and pick up speed on Sunday.
Sunday will be cool with afternoon highs near 50 degrees. Rain is likely in the morning, and we could see a few light shows in the afternoon and evening.
More rain is expected on Monday, and we could see a few snowflakes sneak in early Monday morning. Once that round of rain clears, we will have sunny skies for a few days. Another round of rain is likely on Friday.
Tonight
Showers, mainly after 9pm. Patchy fog after 4am. Low around 40. Calm wind becoming northwest around 5 mph after midnight. Chance of precipitation is 80%. New precipitation amounts between a quarter and half of an inch possible.
Sunday
Showers likely, mainly before noon. Patchy fog before 10am. Otherwise, mostly cloudy, with a high near 48. Breezy, with a northwest wind around 15 mph, with gusts as high as 25 mph. Chance of precipitation is 70%. New precipitation amounts between a tenth and quarter of an inch possible.
Monday
A slight chance of rain and snow showers before 10am, then a chance of rain showers. Mostly sunny, with a high near 46. North wind 5 to 10 mph, with gusts as high as 15 mph. Chance of precipitation is 50%. Little or no snow accumulation expected.
Tuesday
Sunny, with a high near 50. North wind 5 to 10 mph.
Wednesday
Mostly sunny, with a high near 58. Southwest wind 5 to 10 mph, with gusts as high as 20 mph.
Thursday
Sunny, with a high near 64. Breezy, with a south wind 10 to 15 mph, with gusts as high as 25 mph.
Friday
A chance of showers. Mostly sunny, with a high near 65. Breezy, with a south wind around 15 mph, with gusts as high as 25 mph.
Saturday
A chance of showers. Partly sunny, with a high near 58. West wind around 10 mph, with gusts as high as 20 mph.
